                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#150rb">Fol. 150rb</locus>: Qǝne I (Wazema) dedicated to ʾArägawi mänfäsawi.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 150rb: ሰላም፡ ለዮሐንስ፡ እምብዝኃ፡ አንክሮ፡ ወተደሞ፨  ነጽሮተ፡ ሥሉስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ከመ፡ ማዕበለ፡ ባሕር፡ ዘያሠጥሞ፨  ሶበ፡ ኂርውናሁ፡ ነጸሩ፡ ወዘዚአሁ፡ አርምሞ፨  እንዘ፡ ውእቱ፡ ወሬዛ፡ ዘእንበለ፡ ያብጽሕ፡ ዓቅሞ፨  አረጋዊ፡ መንፈሳዊ፡ ሰመይዎ፡ ስሞ፨</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 150rb: Hail to Yoḥannǝs from much of admiration and wonder. Whom the vision of the Trinity submerged like a wave of the sea. When they saw his benevolence and his quietness While he was young and had not grown up yet He was called Spiritual Elder</q>
                           
                        </item>
